      "title": "Poem of the Day: A Summer Wind",
      "pubDate": "2017-06-15 05:00:00",
      "link": "http:\/\/feeds.poetryfoundation.org\/~r\/PoetryFoundation\/PoemOfTheDayText\/~3\/2iBZl-nD01w\/53268",
      "guid": "\/\/www.poetryfoundation.org\/poems-and-poets\/poems\/detail\/53268",
      "author": "Michael Field",
      "thumbnail": "",
      "description": "\n<div>O wind, thou hast thy kingdom in the trees, <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 And all thy royalties <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Sweep through the land to-day. <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 It is mid June, <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>And thou, with all thy instruments in tune,<br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Thine orchestra<br>\n<\/div>\n<div>Of heaving fields and heavy swinging fir, <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Strikest a lay <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 That doth rehearse <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>Her ancient freedom to the universe. <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 All other sound in awe <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Repeats its law: <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 The bird is mute; the sea <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Sucks up its waves; from rain <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 The burthened clouds refrain, <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>To listen to thee in thy leafery, <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Thou unconfined, <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>Lavish, large, soothing, refluent summer wind. <br>\n<\/div>\n<div><br><\/div>\n<div><br><\/div>\n<div class=\"credit\">\n<br><br><h4>Michael Field<\/h4>\n<p class=\"bio\"><a href=\"http:\/\/www.poetryfoundation.org\/poems-and-poets\/poets\/detail\/michael-field\">Biography<\/a><br><a href=\"http:\/\/www.poetryfoundation.org\/poems-and-poets\/poets\/detail\/michael-field#about\" data-view=\"ToTopView\">More poems by this author<\/a><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<img src=\"http:\/\/feeds.feedburner.com\/~r\/PoetryFoundation\/PoemOfTheDayText\/~4\/2iBZl-nD01w\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\">\n",
      "content": "\n<div>O wind, thou hast thy kingdom in the trees, <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 And all thy royalties <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Sweep through the land to-day. <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 It is mid June, <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>And thou, with all thy instruments in tune,<br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Thine orchestra<br>\n<\/div>\n<div>Of heaving fields and heavy swinging fir, <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Strikest a lay <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 That doth rehearse <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>Her ancient freedom to the universe. <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 All other sound in awe <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Repeats its law: <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 The bird is mute; the sea <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Sucks up its waves; from rain <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 The burthened clouds refrain, <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>To listen to thee in thy leafery, <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Thou unconfined, <br>\n<\/div>\n<div>Lavish, large, soothing, refluent summer wind. <br>\n<\/div>\n<div><br><\/div>\n<div><br><\/div>\n<div class=\"credit\">\n<br><br><h4>Michael Field<\/h4>\n<p class=\"bio\"><a href=\"http:\/\/www.poetryfoundation.org\/poems-and-poets\/poets\/detail\/michael-field\">Biography<\/a><br><a href=\"http:\/\/www.poetryfoundation.org\/poems-and-poets\/poets\/detail\/michael-field#about\" data-view=\"ToTopView\">More poems by this author<\/a><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<img src=\"http:\/\/feeds.feedburner.com\/~r\/PoetryFoundation\/PoemOfTheDayText\/~4\/2iBZl-nD01w\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\">\n",
